## Table 3 — cc_versions

The immutable version record created on submit. One row per submitted Compass. Stores the complete intake payload, all synthesis content, version metadata, and completion state. The synthesis JSONB field is the only field that can be updated after creation — only when a legitimate regeneration with changed inputs occurs.

```sql
create table cc_versions (
  id                      uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id                 uuid not null references auth.users(id) on delete cascade,
  version_name            text not null,
  version_number          integer not null,
  input_hash              text not null,
  full_intake_payload     jsonb not null default '{}',
  synthesis               jsonb not null default '{}',
  synthesis_status        text not null default 'pending' check (synthesis_status in ('pending', 'generating', 'complete', 'failed')),
  horizons_complete       text[] not null default '{}',
  scenario_tags_present   text[] not null default '{}',
  is_current_version      boolean not null default true,
  submitted_at            timestamptz not null default now(),
  synthesis_generated_at  timestamptz,
  created_at              timestamptz not null default now()
);

-- Indexes
create index cc_versions_user_id_idx on cc_versions(user_id);
create index cc_versions_user_current_idx on cc_versions(user_id, is_current_version);
create index cc_versions_input_hash_idx on cc_versions(user_id, input_hash);

-- RLS
alter table cc_versions enable row level security;

create policy "Users can read their own versions"
  on cc_versions
  for select
  using (auth.uid() = user_id);

create policy "Users can insert their own versions"
  on cc_versions
  for insert
  with check (auth.uid() = user_id);

create policy "Users can update synthesis on their own versions"
  on cc_versions
  for update
  using (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

**synthesis JSONB structure:**

