**Notes:**

`input_hash` is a deterministic hash of the full intake payload. Used by the regenerate logic to determine whether inputs have changed since the last synthesis. If the hash matches the current version, overwrite synthesis. If it does not match, write a new version record.

`is_current_version` is set to true on creation and set to false on all previous versions for that user when a new version is created. Enables fast retrieval of the current version without sorting.

`horizons_complete` and `scenario_tags_present` are arrays of horizon identifiers — e.g. `['12_month', '24_month', '36_month', 'ultimate_vision']` — stored at version creation time for fast display in the History tab without needing to inspect the full payload.

