## Table 4 — cc_version_horizon_snapshots

Stores the per-horizon field state as individual queryable rows within a version. While the full intake payload is also stored in `cc_versions.full_intake_payload`, this table enables horizon-level querying, comparison between versions at the horizon level, and clean data access for the Progression Synthesis feature without parsing the full version JSONB.

```sql
create table cc_version_horizon_snapshots (
  id                  uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  version_id          uuid not null references cc_versions(id) on delete cascade,
  user_id             uuid not null references auth.users(id) on delete cascade,
  horizon             text not null check (horizon in ('12_month', '24_month', '36_month', 'ultimate_vision')),
  field_selections    jsonb not null default '{}',
  scenario_id         uuid references gvs_saved_growth_scenarios(id) on delete set null,
  scenario_snapshot   jsonb,
  created_at          timestamptz not null default now(),

  unique (version_id, horizon)
);

-- Indexes
create index cc_version_horizon_snapshots_version_id_idx on cc_version_horizon_snapshots(version_id);
create index cc_version_horizon_snapshots_user_id_idx on cc_version_horizon_snapshots(user_id);
create index cc_version_horizon_snapshots_user_horizon_idx on cc_version_horizon_snapshots(user_id, horizon);

-- RLS
alter table cc_version_horizon_snapshots enable row level security;

create policy "Users can read their own horizon snapshots"
  on cc_version_horizon_snapshots
  for select
  using (auth.uid() = user_id);

create policy "Users can insert their own horizon snapshots"
  on cc_version_horizon_snapshots
  for insert
  with check (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

**Notes:**

This table is written to at the same time as `cc_versions` on submit — four rows created per submission, one per horizon. It is never updated after creation. Its primary future-state purpose is enabling the Pro tier Progression Synthesis feature, which will query across versions at the horizon level to surface how specific dimensions have shifted over time.

