## Table 5 — cc_meta

A single row per founder. Tracks the current navigation and draft state at a high level. Enables fast retrieval of where a founder is in their Clarity Compass journey without querying multiple tables. Updated on every meaningful state change.

```sql
create table cc_meta (
  id                      uuid primary key default gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id                 uuid not null references auth.users(id) on delete cascade,
  current_version_id      uuid references cc_versions(id) on delete set null,
  has_submitted           boolean not null default false,
  last_active_horizon     text check (last_active_horizon in ('12_month', '24_month', '36_month', 'ultimate_vision')),
  draft_overall_status    text not null default 'not_started' check (draft_overall_status in ('not_started', 'in_progress', 'complete')),
  version_count           integer not null default 0,
  last_activity_at        timestamptz not null default now(),
  created_at              timestamptz not null default now(),

  unique (user_id)
);

-- Indexes
create index cc_meta_user_id_idx on cc_meta(user_id);

-- RLS
alter table cc_meta enable row level security;

create policy "Users can manage their own meta record"
  on cc_meta
  for all
  using (auth.uid() = user_id)
  with check (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

**Notes:**

`current_version_id` references the most recently submitted version. Used as the primary pointer for the Dashboard — if this is populated, render the synthesis from that version record.

`has_submitted` is the single boolean that determines whether the Dashboard shows the empty state or the loaded synthesis.

`draft_overall_status` is a rolled-up status derived from the four horizon draft completion statuses. Updated whenever any horizon draft is saved.

`version_count` increments on every new version creation. Used for display in the History tab and for determining version numbering.

